  "text": "The Grafana codebase contains a comprehensive migration system to convert legacy alerting rules to unified alerting (ngalert). The system is organized in three main components:\n\n## Legacy Alerting Engine\nThe legacy alerting system is defined in `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/alert_mig.go` (github.com/sg-evals/grafana--26d36ec), which contains the database schema for the old alert table structure. Legacy alerting has been removed in Grafana v11, as evidenced by the checks in `pkg/setting/setting.go` that prevent enabling legacy alerting.\n\n## Unified Alerting (ngalert) Engine\nThe unified alerting engine is implemented in `pkg/services/ngalert/` with the following key components:\n\n1. **Data Models** (`pkg/services/ngalert/models/alert_rule.go`): Defines the `AlertRule` struct for unified alerting with properties like ID, GUID, OrgID, Title, Condition, Data, UID, NamespaceUID, RuleGroup, NoDataState, and ExecErrState.\n\n2. **Storage Layer** (`pkg/services/ngalert/store/`): \n   - `alert_rule.go`: Implements alert rule persistence\n   - `alertmanager.go`: Manages alertmanager configurations\n   - `database.go`: Database abstraction layer\n   - These files implement the DBstore interface for unified alert rule storage\n\n3. **Main Service** (`pkg/services/ngalert/ngalert.go`): The AlertNG service orchestrates all alerting components including metrics, API handlers, scheduler, notifier, and provisioning services.\n\n4. **Provisioning** (`pkg/services/ngalert/provisioning/`): \n   - `alert_rules.go`: AlertRuleService with CreateAlertRule, UpdateAlertRule, DeleteAlertRule methods\n   - `persist.go`: Persistence interface definitions\n   - `compat.go`: Compatibility layer for converting between formats\n\n5. **Notifier** (`pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/`):\n   - `receiver_svc.go`: Receiver service for managing notification channels\n   - `crypto.go`: Encryption/decryption for sensitive configuration\n   - `legacy_storage/`: Handles legacy alertmanager configuration compatibility\n\n## Migration System\nThe migration from legacy to unified alerting is implemented in `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/ualert/` with multiple migration files:\n\n1. **ualert.go**: Core migration entry point containing:\n   - `FixEarlyMigration()`: Fixes organizations and alertmanager configuration files created before v8.2\n   - `upgradeNgAlerting`: Migration struct that handles organization ID assignments\n   - `updateAlertmanagerFiles()`: Moves alertmanager configuration files to organization-specific directories\n\n2. **tables.go**: Defines database schema migrations:\n   - `AddTablesMigrations()`: Creates alert_rule, alert_rule_version, alert_instance, alert_configuration tables\n   - `addAlertRuleMigrations()`: Creates the alert_rule table with columns for org_id, title, condition, data, interval_seconds, namespace_uid, rule_group\n   - `addAlertmanagerConfigMigrations()`: Creates alert_configuration table for storing alertmanager configurations\n   - Includes index creation and column modifications for schema evolution\n\n3. **org_upgrade_state_mig.go**: Tracks alerting type per organization (Legacy vs UnifiedAlerting)\n\n4. **created_folders_mig.go**: Migrates records of folders created during the legacy alert migration process\n\n5. **migration_service_migration.go**: Moves legacy alert migration status from migration log to kvstore with namespace \"ngalert.migration\"\n\n6. **accesscontrol/alerting.go**: Migrates alerting-related permissions and action names\n\n## Legacy Storage Bridges\nMultiple legacy storage implementations provide compatibility between old and new systems:\n\n1. **Alertmanager Configuration**: `pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/config.go` implements `alertmanagerConfigStoreImpl` for reading/writing legacy Alertmanager configurations\n\n2. **Receiver Management**: `pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/legacy_storage/` contains:\n   - `receivers.go`: Manages receiver CRUD operations with conversion functions\n   - `compat.go`: Implements `ReceiverToPostableApiReceiver()` and `PostableApiReceiverToReceiver()` for format conversion\n   - `errors.go`: Error definitions for receiver operations\n\n3. **REST API Bridges**:\n   - `pkg/registry/apps/alerting/rules/alertrule/legacy_storage.go`: Legacy REST API storage for alert rules\n   - `pkg/registry/apps/alerting/rules/recordingrule/legacy_storage.go`: Legacy storage for recording rules\n   - `pkg/registry/apps/alerting/notifications/receiver/legacy_storage.go`: Legacy storage for receivers\n   - `pkg/registry/apps/alerting/notifications/routingtree/legacy_storage.go`: Legacy storage for routing trees\n   - `pkg/registry/apps/alerting/notifications/timeinterval/legacy_storage.go`: Legacy storage for time intervals\n   - `pkg/registry/apps/alerting/notifications/templategroup/legacy_storage.go`: Legacy storage for notification templates\n\n## Provisioning\nThe provisioning system (`pkg/services/provisioning/`) handles alert rule configuration:\n- `provisioning.go`: Orchestrates alerting provisioning including rule service, folder service, and receiver configuration\n- `alerting/rules_provisioner.go`: Implements the provisioning logic for alert rules from configuration files\n\n## Configuration\nUnified alerting configuration is defined in `pkg/setting/setting_unified_alerting.go` with `UnifiedAlertingSettings` struct that includes:\n- AdminConfigPollInterval\n- AlertmanagerConfigPollInterval\n- DefaultConfiguration\n- ExecuteAlerts\n- BaseInterval\n- RulesPerRuleGroupLimit\n\nThe migration system ensures that when users upgrade from legacy alerting to unified alerting, their alert rules and configurations are automatically converted while maintaining backward compatibility through legacy storage implementations."
}

